26 2021-01-02 ringing in ears Myalgias starting within 1 hour after vaccination, worsened throughout day that radiated to ipsilate... Read more
Close
Myalgias starting within 1 hour after vaccination, worsened throughout day that radiated to ipsilateral trapezius and rhomboid areas. Starting around 16 hours after vaccination, severe subjective fevers and chills with severe headache that worsened with lying down. The headache was the most concerning symptom with tinnitus when laying flat in supine. It awoke me from sleep and prevented me from laying flat so I had to sleep upright on the couch. I took tylenol 500mg around 0200 and was able to sleep for a few hours. By 24 hours post vaccine, the headache and fevers/chills significantly improved so I could attend work the next day.
26 2021-01-03 eye itchiness, eye swelling After receiving the vaccine in the morning, patient developed eye swelling later on that evening, fo... Read more
Close
After receiving the vaccine in the morning, patient developed eye swelling later on that evening, for which he took diphenhydramine 50 mg orally once. He felt better the next day, however the swelling came back the following day (12/24) in addition to eye itchiness. He was prescribed prednisone 60 mg orally daily for 5 days and diphenhydramine 50 mg q6h.
26 2021-01-03 mouth pain his gums became discolored and turned purple/gums (both sides up and down) remain purple/discolorati... Read more
Close
his gums became discolored and turned purple/gums (both sides up and down) remain purple/discoloration to the gums in his mouth; his mouth started hurting; feeling hot; Body aches; Fever; Pain to the gums in his mouth; muscle aches; sore throat; neck pain; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). A 26-year-old male patient received the first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection, lot number and expiration date were not reported), via an unspecified route of administration to right shoulder on 24Dec2020 11:30 at a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. There were no medical history and concomitant medications. The patient received vaccine on 24Dec2020. He experienced body aches, fever, and feeling hot with onset of about 3-4 hours after he was administered (24Dec2020). Next day (25Dec2020), his mouth started hurting, his gums became discolored and turned purple. Gums (both sides up and down) remained purple. He will be seeing a dentist. He also reported pain and discoloration to the gums in his mouth on 25Dec2020. He had been experiencing some of the regular side effects such as muscle aches, sore throat, neck pain on an unspecified date in Dec2020. Outcome of the event gum discoloration was not recovered, of the events feeling hot, generelized aching, and fever was recovered on 26Dec2020, of the event gum pain was recovering, and of the remaining events was unknown. He reported seriousness criteria as what he thinks to be medically significant at this point; that they could be medically significant. He is scheduled to receive the second dose of the product which at this point he does not plan to change. Dose change is unknown until he determines cause of these events and on what the doctor and dentist he is going to see recommend. He believes events could be caused by the vaccine. Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.; Sender's Comments: A causal association between BNT162 and the reported events cannot be excluded based on a compatible temporal relation. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to RAs, Ethics Committees, and Investigators, as appropriate.

Allergic reaction resulting in full body hives, swollen hands, eyelids and lips; Allergic reaction resulting in full body hives, swollen hands, eyelids and lips; Allergic reaction resulting in full body hives, swollen hands, eyelids and lips; Allergic reaction resulting in full body hives, swollen hands, eyelids and lips; Allergic reaction resulting in full body hives, swollen hands, eyelids and lips; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable other health professional (patient). A 27-year-old male patient received first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection, lot number and expiry date were unknown) at the age of 26 years old, via intramuscular route in the left arm, on 10Jan2021 at 13:00, at a single dose, for COVID-19 immunization. Outcome of the events was recovering. The patient has not been tested for COVID-19 since vaccination. Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.

Runny nose; tachycardia; Weakness; flu like symptoms; Sore/dry throat; Sore/dry throat; nausea; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). A 26-year-old male patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), intramuscularly on the left arm, first dose on 18Dec2020 (lot number: EH9899) and second dose on 08Jan2021 08:15 (lot number: EL3246), both at a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. 26 2021-01-27 vision blurred, double vision After receiving the first dose of the COVID vaccine I was experiencing headaches, dizziness, lighthe... Read more
Close
After receiving the first dose of the COVID vaccine I was experiencing headaches, dizziness, lightheadedness, palpitations, and nausea. The first dose was on 12/21/20. These symptoms resolved around 12/26/20. I received the second dose of the COVID vaccine on 01/11/21. I began experiencing symptoms on 01/12/21. The symptoms I was experiencing were lightheadedness, dizziness, and brain fog/confusion. These symptoms got significantly worse from 01/13/21 - 01/24/21 and I began developing profound confusion/brain fog, diplopia, blurry vision, headaches, feeling like I'm swaying on a boat, and the "feeling of being drunk". As of 01/25/21, the symptoms have seemed to get better and I am starting to feel more like myself. The drunk feeling and mild blurry vision are still present as of today 01/28/21.
26 2021-02-01 lip swelling Patient experienced flu like symptoms the morning after receiving his vaccine (1/29). Symptoms impr... Read more
Close
Patient experienced flu like symptoms the morning after receiving his vaccine (1/29). Symptoms improved by 1/31). On 2/1, patient woke up with a rash all over his body that was pruritic. Patient took Benadryl which helped improve his symptoms. Today (2/2), patient woke up with angioedema. He took another Benadryl--symptoms improved. Denies SOB, tongue swelling, itchy throat, or wheezing. Swelling is localized to lips only.
26 2021-02-10 swelling around the eyes Patient presented with puffy eyes approximately 4 minutes after vaccination. Was alert and oriented ... Read more
Close
Patient presented with puffy eyes approximately 4 minutes after vaccination. Was alert and oriented to time, person, and place upon questioning and was able to engage in conversation. Parent (mother) of patient was present who gave patient's medical history and reported allergy to grass with similar reaction. Blood pressure was taken and found to be 150/80. Mother reported patient had not taken his blood pressure medicine yet that day but his normal is 115/70 with medication. While nurse was assessing patient's pulse (patient's pulse was WNL at 85) and other nursing staff was obtaining medication to administer if needed after assessment, patient became unresponsive to verbal commands and his upper body became limp. At 1054, a one time, single dose of 50 mg of diphenhydramine IM was given in the left deltoid. On site EMT arrived on the scene at 1055, completed assessment, and confirmed giving diphenhydramine was the best course of action. At this time, 1055, patient became responsive to verbal commands and was oriented to time, place, and person. At 1056 O2 sat was at 97%, pulse 70, and at 1100, BP was 110/70. Patient stayed for observation 30 more minutes and remained stable. Patient and parent were educated on side effects of diphenhydramine, to watch for any returning symptoms of allergic reaction throughout the day, and if/when to head to the ER. Recommended patient not receive 2nd dose of COVID vaccination.

26 2021-03-04 tongue itchiness I took notes during my wait time: -6 minutes in my throat felt weird, but different than normal alle... Read more
Close
I took notes during my wait time: -6 minutes in my throat felt weird, but different than normal allergic reactions to foods. I prepared my Epi-Pen so I have easier access at this time. -9 minutes in the sides of my tongue were slightly itchy. -11 minutes in and I felt as though the saliva in the back of my throat was thicker and I needed to clear my throat a bit more often, similar to allergic reactions. -15 minutes in, I felt my heart pound once out of beat, but my heart rhythm returned to normal immediately. Tongue itchiness also became intermittent rather than constant. -18 minutes in, overall condition improved and I felt better. -22 minutes in, my throat felt scratchy like I would if I consumed legumes (chickpeas, green peas, soy beans, etc.) but also oddly warm, which was out of the norm. No treatments needed given mild reactions. I went to work, but notified my co-workers of my reaction, so if my condition worsens they can help administer my Epi-Pen. I am reporting this at 9:21 am on 03/05/2021, roughly an hour after my first dose.

This was my second dose of the Pfizer/BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. I took some notes during my waiting time following my injection similar to my first dose. Information from my last report can be found using Temporary VAERS E-Report No: 334845. Of note, I did prepare for my second dose by taking Benadryl 50 mg and Airborne Immune-Boost supplements the night before my second dose, so my symptoms were not as severe as last time. 6 minutes: Mild tingling around tongue. This time all around the edges of my tongue, but a lot less bothersome than the first dose. 8 minutes: Weird. Slight itchiness under left half of tongue. Still very mild but less concerning than first dose itchiness on the left and right sides of my tongue. 18 minutes: Itchy on right side slightly, only side noticeable. 20 minutes: Mild warm feeling on left side of top of my throat. Less bothersome than time. 26 minutes: Left throat warm ness resolved, but transitioned to right side of top of my throat. 31 minute: Throat warmness overall resolved, but slightly itchy on edge of right side of my tongue. 37 minutes: Top of throat on right feels weird but not itchy. Warm maybe? 39 minutes: Weird feeling on right side of throat resolved. Symptoms more or less resolved the rest of the day, especially after second dose of Flonase @ 9:00 am. 14 hours later: About to go to bed. Feeling fatigued, similar to my first dose after working out. Took airborne and two Benadryl (25 mg each) before sleeping. 24 hours later: 03/27/2021, feeling more fatigued, groggy, mild headache (mostly at back of my head), and muscle aches around my body. 25 hours later: Groggy feeling and fatigue resolved. Possibly due to Benadryl or vaccine? 32 hours later: Majority of muscle aches resolved. Headache also resolved. Feeling mostly soreness at this point. Drank Airborne @ 10:00 am and 4:00 pm. In between drank plenty of fluids (water, cranberry juice, apple juice, milk). No fever or chills.

lost my vision; lost my vision and hearing; essentially unresponsive; feel light-headed; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 27-year-old male patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE, lot number: EW0161), dose 1 via an unspecified route of administration, administered in the left arm on 16Apr2021 at 14:30 as SINGLE DOSE (at the age of 27 years-old) for covid-19 immunisation. Medical history included coarctation of the aorta from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing coarctation of aorta (age: 3 months), only requires bi-annual cardiologist visits, loss of consciousness from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing, covid-19 from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing. Prior to the vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19. The patient did not receive any concomitant medications. The patient had no know allergies. The patient did not receive any other vaccine within 4 weeks prior to the vaccine. The patient lost his vision and hearing, essentially unresponsive and light-headed on 16Apr2021 at 14:30. Circulation issues leading to a black out. Within 60 seconds of getting the shot, he began to feel light-headed. Within 30 seconds of that, he knew he needed help, so alerted the emergency medical technicians (EMTs) via car horn/flashers. By the time they arrived (120 seconds from the initial shot), he lost his vision and hearing and was essentially unresponsive. They woke him enough to unlock my car door, at which point they had him lay back to improve his circulation. That ultimately worked and got him back to normal within about 5 minutes. The patient had issues like this before relating to a coarctation of his aorta which he had done at 3 months of age. Over the years, he has "blacked out" like this from weight lifting and other high exertion things. This was the first time it was induced without him overexerting himself, and the onset of the "blackout" was much quicker than what he had experienced from weightlifting. Normally, he could tell 1-3 minutes in advance that he would black out. This time, it was about 30 seconds. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of lost vision and hearing, essentially unresponsive and feel light-headed. EMTs did an electrocardiogram (EKG) and blood glucose check. The outcome of lost his vision and hearing, essentially unresponsive and light-headed was recovered on an unknown date. It was also reported that since the vaccination, the patient had not been tested for COVID-19.

After about an hour following my second COVID-19 Injection I began feeling warm. My forehead felt warmer so I figure I may have had a slight fever at that point. I received a metallic (Note I say metallic but I know it wasn't actually metal but that's simply the best way I can describe the taste I experienced) following the injection about 5 minutes after. My arm remained sore following and still remains sore as of this report. I experienced a decline in mental acuity following about an hour after injection. I began to feel lightheaded and exhausted to the point I was experiencing severe disorientation and confusion. I was having trouble putting sentences together and experienced a ringing sensation in the ears. I felt like I wasn't even present anymore. I couldn't comprehend things around me and apparently had conversations I don't even remember having. Note that at that point I had gotten home but don't even remember getting home. I just know that this did not begin to wear off until around 8:45pm when it was like someone flipped a switch and I suddenly was coherent again. It was an odd sensation to experience. The arm remained sore and the metallic taste returned briefly after this experience. I experienced a similar feeling from the HPV injection years ago, but just like this it was a temporary thing that resulted in no long term issues. However, I cannot tell you fully what we did the rest of the day until around 845-9 pm. I also remember becoming partly agitated after the injection like my body just all of a sudden took notice of something and shot into action. I had received my allergy injections this same day about two hours earlier as well and none of these reactions ever occur with those for me. I continued to drink liquid as far as I know as there were a few empty bottles of water next to me. I have no recollection of getting them. It's odd. There's just this brief moment in time that is just missing from my memory with a few short bits and pieces that are there like a puzzle with some missing pieces. I feel I became so fatigued I could not function. My emotions I remember were off and hard to control during this period too. I felt like I was having some random mood swings. I feel ok now though aside from the upset stomach occasionally and the fatigue and arm pain (but even the arm pain has partly decreased now). It all ceased. I have a number of health issues outside of this but have not experienced this long of a period of almost intermittent amnesia and incoherency following an injection before. I believe it made me that much more tired or reacted with one of my many conditions or genetic variants that perhaps may have been part of this. I'm happy to provide anything I can to help with this. I am greatly appreciative of all the CDC has done to get us this vaccine and continues to do to ensure our safety both before and after injection. It is commendable. I did fill out my survey through the V-Safe portal as well and will continue to follow up there should I have any changes. I have not sought medical care following this event as the coherency and such have seemed to resolve in regards to the vaccine injection. Only thing left are known side effects at this point besides an occasional increase in numbness and tingling that I already experience in my legs and feet. My absolute best guess for the cause is my immune system which already has some issues regulating (doesn't always like to learn everything it should and we are currently searching for an undiagnosed autoimmune disorder currently going on as well in me) on top of allergy shots today. it was perhaps just a bit too much demand on it all at once. But it seems to be balancing out again now.

I noticed during this time that I was getting very sweaty. My skin over my whole body seemed to me to be damp from sweat and where I checked I was sweating visibly (no droplets formed? it was just dampness). At the same time I experienced nausea. I believed that I might throw up, so I requested something to throw up into. I never threw up. I continued to get more and more dizzy and I had trouble remaining upright (while seated). A woman observing me stated afterward that my eyes rolled back and that I fainted. I do not believe that I actually fainted because I remember hearing her tell the pharmacist that I had passed out. I had my eyes closed though, so it is possible that I fainted briefly. The pharmacist called 911. I began to feel better approximately 15 minutes after receiving the vaccine. I stopped sweating, and then the nausea subsided, and then my dizziness cleared up. The EMTs arrived approximately 20 minutes after I received the vaccine and took my blood pressure. I do not remember the reading, but the EMT stated that it was not elevated. My blood oxygen was 99%. The EMT waited about 10 minutes and took my blood pressure again. He stated that it was higher, but not concerning. The EMT waited another 10-15 minutes and then left. Before he left, the EMT stated to me that I was one of 2 concurrent calls regarding adverse vaccine responses. After this event I drank a bottle of water. It did not seem to have an impact. I have not received vaccinations since I was a child. I do not remember adverse reactions to injections when I was a child. I did pass out when giving blood approximately 12 years ago. I have always attributed this to the fact that I did not eat or drink for 20 hours prior to donating blood.

My ears started ringing louder and more pronounced, which I assumed was a side-effect of the headache and/or immune response to the vaccine. It's past two weeks now since dose 1 and my ears are still ringing much more loudly and noticeably than in the last 15 or so years. All other side effects have long ago subsided. It seems to be worse in left ear, the same side I got shot on. I imagine that's irrelevant, but mentioning it anyway here. Distracting and distressing. Am scheduled for a second dose on April 21 and now hesitant about getting it.

Response: Spoke from EUA PI (Revised: 06 April 2021) under Post Authorization Experience Fact Sheet for Recipients and Caregivers (Revised: 06 April 2021) under section WHAT ARE THE RISKS OF THE PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE? As noted in the Fact Sheet for Recipients, you should not get the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine if you had a severe allergic reaction after a previous dose of the vaccine or if you had a severe allergic reaction to any ingredient of the vaccine. The decision to receive the second dose for any other reason cannot be made by Pfizer. We refer you to speak to your healthcare provider about the risks of the vaccine compared to the risks of potentially not being fully protected against COVID-19 infection. Your healthcare provider knows your health situation and has access to information that can better help inform this decision. Left ear tinnitus; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable Consumer (Patient). A 39-Year-old Male patient received first dose of BNT162B2 (Pfizer BioNTech Covid 19 MRNA VACCINE BIONTECH) (Lot/batch no: EP7534) via an unspecified route, administered in to Left Arm on 2 16Mar2021, 12:30 PM as single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. The patient's medical history was not reported. Concomitant drugs were taken, but the medications prescribed were not reported. Prior to the vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19 and didn't had a COVID-19 test since vaccination. The patient didn't receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine and he is not Allergic to medications, food, or other products. The patient experienced Left ear tinnitus on 16Mar2021, 10:00 PM. No therapeutic measures were taken for the event. The clinical outcome of the Left ear tinnitus was not recovered. No follow-up attempts are needed. No further information is expected.

Fever; Chills; Headache; I have both my eyes swollen; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable consumer (reporting on himself). A 39-years-old male patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Formulation: Solution for injection, Lot Number and Expiration Date was not reported) via an unspecified route of administration in Arm Left on 20May2021 11:45, as 2nd dose, single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient medical history nad concomitant medications were not reported. Patient previously took first dose of BNT162B2 29Apr2021 11:45. Prior to vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19 and did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine and any other medications the patient received within 2 weeks of vaccination. He had his second shot on 20May2021 11:45 and he went to fever, chills and headache until Saturday morning. 23May2021 late in the evening he noticed his eyes started swelling up a little bit; they went down a little bit and he went to bed; 24May2021 he woke up with swollen eyes again. He clarified that he already reported this information; but he was unable to obtain reference number from that report. He had questions regarding these side effects after the Pfizer Covid Vaccine and wanted to know about recommendation on taking histamines like Zyrtec Benadryl after the vaccine Response. Since the vaccination, the patient has tested for COVID-19. The outcome of the event i have both my eyes swollen was not recovered and for rest events was unknown. Information about lot/batch number has been requested.
